  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "To avert from men God&#39;s wrath Jesus suffered in our stead; By an ignominious death He a full atonement made; And by His most precious blood, Brought us, sinners, nigh to God.",
    "v2": "That we never should forget This great Love on us bestowed, He gave us His flesh to eat, and to drink His precious blood; All who sick and needy are May receive in Him a share.",
    "v3": "Hither each afflicted soul May repair, though filled with grief; To the sick, not to the whole, the Physician brings relief; Fear not, therefore, but draw nigh, Christ will all your wants supply.",
    "v4": "He who in self\\- righteousness Fixes any hope or stay, Has not on a wedding dress, And with shame is sent away; To the hungry, weary heart, He will food and rest impart.",
    "v5": "But examine first your case, Whether you be in the faith; Do you long for pard&#39;ning grace? Is your only hope His death? Then, howe&#39;er your soul&#39;s oppressed, Come, you are a worthy guest."
  },
